<p>Flyers can be an effective way of generating interest  in  the  program. Flyers are designed to display a little more information about the program than other resources.  Effective ways   to use flyers include:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>More Detail</strong>: These flyers are more like brochures in that they have more detail than the posters, and can be used in similar ways.</li>
<li><strong>Give them to local leaders &amp; Institutes</strong>: Take a    stack to your local Institute and ask them to set them out. Give them to    local priesthood leaders. This will keep the program in the front of    their minds and makes it easier for them to refer students. Give them  to   LDS Services and Employment where possible.&nbsp; <strong><br /></strong></li>
<li><strong>Cross Pollinate:</strong> If Pathway is not a good fit, think about Concurrent Enrollment, Online Degrees, or campus programs. </li>
</ul>
